text:
No. 70 Pine Street (Sixty Wall Tower); on the west side of Pearl Street, from Pine to Cedar Streets.

(1)

A general view south from 60 Wall Street, between Pearl and William Streets, showing the New York Bay, the Statue of Liberty (Bedloes Island), the Battery (extreme southern part of the city) and the tower of the Farmer's Loan and Trust Company, 22 William Street (between Beaver Street and Exchange Place) in the right foreground.

July 1, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

The same, a closer view.

July 1, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)

The same, a year later.

February 9, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
title: General view - Pine Street - South.
